Q1. Take arrays with different data types and perform type conversions.

In [1]:
import numpy as np
In [2]:
# 1
a = np.array([1,2,3,4])
print(a.dtype)

int32
In [25]:
a = a.astype('int8')
print(a.dtype)

int8
In [8]:
# 2
a2 = np.array([1,2,3,255])
print(a2.dtype)

int32
In [26]:
a2 = a2.astype('uint8')
print(a2.dtype)

uint8
In [12]:
# 3
a3 = np.array([1,2,3,-55])
print(a3.dtype)

int32
In [27]:
a3 = a3.astype('int8')
print(a3.dtype)

int8
In [31]:
# 4
a4 =np.array([1,2,3,30115])
print(a4.dtype)

int32
In [32]:
a4 = a4.astype('uint16')
print(a4.dtype)

uint16
In [19]:
# 5
a5 = np.array([1,2,3,1000])
print(a5.dtype)

a5 = a5.astype('int16')

Slicing¶

In [52]:

Out[52]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1ff5b6d5f50>
In [54]:

<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1ff5b7bae10>

Stacking¶

In [59]:
c = a[: ,400:]
In [61]:
plt.imshow(np.hstack((a,c)))
Out[61]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1ff5b9c5ad0>
In [62]:
d = a[500:2000]
In [63]:
plt.imshow(np.vstack((d,a)))

<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1ff5a4f3d10>
